From Ian J Hogg Subject Re How do I find my AppContext In article qvatv Todd Greene writes Is there an Xt call to give me my application context I am fixing up an X Motif program, and am trying to use XtAppAddTimeOut, whose first argument is the app context What call can I use to give me this value You can get the ApplicationContext associated with a widget by calling XtWidgetToApplicationContext Ian Hogg